    <svcsubsec id="x08290214">
        <title>PANEL LIGHTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f082901126" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G082901126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Panel Lights Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER (ESC)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DRIVETRAIN 1939 DATA LINK BETWEEN ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER (EGC) AND ESC</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. EGC</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DIMMER CIRCUITS CONTROLLED BY PANEL LIGHT SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DIMMER SWITCH MOUNTED IN 3 SWITCH PACK MOUNTED IN EGC</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f082901126">Panel Lights Function Diagram</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>Panel lights are low wattage bulbs that illuminate gauges and other miscellaneous items. The panel
                light switch provides input to the EGC which generates the voltage to dim/brighten the panel lights for
                the gauge clusters, speedometer/tachometer module, heater control, etc.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
